## [1.16.80-alpha] - 2026-06-11

### Sprint 36d â LOCI identity marker register $0319

Found while building a Phosphoric-based automated test harness for
locifilemanager-v2 (LOCI Oric Atmos client app): `loci_present()` in
client software detects LOCI hardware via `peek($0319) == 'L'`, a
convention from real loci-firmware (`mia.c`: `IOREGS(0x0319) = 'L'` set
once at init, writes thereafter silently ignored â "Disabled write for
LOCI identity marker"). $0319 falls in the $0310-$031B I/O range LOCI's
RP2040 claims, but Phosphoric's LOCI DSK emulation only covered
$0310-$0314 + $0318, so reads of $0319 fell through to VIA and any LOCI
client app's presence check failed under `--loci`/`--loci-flash`.

#### Added

- `LOCI_DSK_IO_ID` ($0319): read returns `'L'` (0x4C) whenever LOCI is
  enabled, `0xFF` otherwise; writes are a no-op, matching real hardware.
- 2 new unit tests in `tests/unit/test_loci.c`
  (`test_dsk_id_register_returns_loci_marker`,
  `test_dsk_id_register_ff_when_disabled`).

