       JSR  WriteLeader
       LDA  #$24
       JSR  PutByte                ; sync byte
       LDX  #$09
$E611: LDA  $02A7,X                ; â buffer $02A8..$02B0
       JSR  PutByte
       DEX
       BNE  $E611
```

Mapping mÃĐmoire â tape (X=9..1) :

| Adresse | Byte tape | Sens |
|---------|-----------|------|
| `$02B0` | #1 | padding |
| `$02AF` | #2 | padding |
| `$02AE` | #3 | type (0x00=BASIC, 0x80=array, 0xC0=string) |
| `$02AD` | #4 | auto-flag (0xC7 si autorun, 0x00 sinon) |
| `$02AC` | #5 | end_hi |
| `$02AB` | #6 | end_lo |
| `$02AA` | #7 | start_hi |
| `$02A9` | #8 | start_lo |
| `$02A8` | #9 | null sep |

Avantages vs TXTTAB/VARTAB :
- Subsume BASIC + machine-code CSAVE (`,A start,E end`) sans casse
- Auto-flag rÃĐel respectÃĐ (0x00 quand l'utilisateur n'a pas demandÃĐ)
- type byte rÃĐel (BASIC/array/string distincts si CSAVE typÃĐ)

ImplÃĐmentation data-driven via `rom_patches_t` :
```c
