## [1.1.2-alpha] - 2026-02-27

### VSync CB1 Improvements (Sprint 19c)

#### Changed
- **PAL timing constants**: replaced `CYCLES_PER_FRAME = 1000000/50` (20000)
  with real PAL values: 312 lines x 64 cycles = 19968 cycles/frame.
  New constants: `PAL_LINES_PER_FRAME`, `PAL_CYCLES_PER_LINE`, `VSYNC_START_LINE`,
  `VSYNC_CYCLE` (16384 = line 256 x 64 cycles).
- **VSync mid-frame trigger**: VSync CB1 pulse now fires at line 256 (cycle
  16384) inside the frame loop instead of at the end of frame, matching real
  ULA timing. CB1 goes low (falling edge) at VSYNC_CYCLE, then returns high
  after the frame loop completes.
- **Edge-triggered CB1**: new `via_set_cb1()` function implements proper edge
  detection using PCR bit 4 (0=falling edge, 1=rising edge). IFR CB1 flag is
  only set on the correct edge transition. Added `cb1_pin` field to `via6522_t`.
- **Legacy `via_trigger_cb1()`**: refactored to use `via_set_cb1()` internally
  (complete pulse: highâlowâhigh).
- **IER guard on VSync trigger**: emulation loop only generates VSync CB1 pulse
  when software has enabled CB1 in VIA IER (`emu->via.ier & VIA_INT_CB1`),
  preventing disruption of ROM keyboard scan IRQ timing.

#### Fixed
- **`via_check_irq()` transition-only notification**: the IRQ callback to the
  CPU is now called only when the /IRQ line state **changes** (assertâdeassert
  or deassertâassert), not on every IFR/IER modification. Added `irq_line`
  field to `via6522_t` to track the current /IRQ output level. This prevents
  spurious `cpu_irq_clear(IRQF_VIA)` when unrelated IFR bits (e.g. CB1) change
  while no matching IER bit is set, which was causing loss of pending T1 IRQs
  and breaking the ROM keyboard scan.
- **Removed IER guards from VSync trigger**: CB1 now fires unconditionally
  like real hardware. Programs polling IFR bit 4 without enabling CB1 in IER
  will work correctly. The transition-only fix in `via_check_irq` makes this
  safe.

#### Added
- **5 new CB1 edge detection tests**: falling edge trigger, rising edge trigger,
  wrong edge no trigger, same state no trigger, clear and retrigger.
- Total: 168 tests (163 + 5), 100% pass rate.

## [1.1.1-alpha] - 2026-02-27

### VSync CB1 Signal (Sprint 19b)

#### Fixed
- **VSync signal on VIA CB1**: the ULA VSync pulse is now generated at the
  end of each frame (50 Hz) by calling `via_trigger_cb1()` in the emulation
  loop. On real Oric hardware, the ULA drives CB1 at vertical retrace so
  software can poll IFR bit 4 (`VIA_INT_CB1 = 0x10`) or enable the CB1
  interrupt to synchronize with the display. Previously this signal was never
  generated, causing programs relying on VBlank synchronization to malfunction.
- All 163 tests pass (no regression)

## [1.1.0-alpha] - 2026-02-24

### Interactive Debugger (Sprint 19)

#### Added
- **Interactive debugger module** (`src/debugger.c`, `include/debugger.h`):
  REPL-based debugger with stdin/stdout command interface
- **Breakpoints**: up to 16 PC breakpoints (`b addr`, `bd n`, `b` to list)
- **Watchpoints**: up to 8 memory write watchpoints (`w addr`, `wd n`, `w` to list)
  using `memory_set_trace()` callback for hardware-level detection
- **Single-step**: `s`/`step` executes one instruction and re-enters REPL
- **Step-over**: `n`/`next` steps over JSR (temporary breakpoint at PC+3)
- **Continue**: `c`/`continue` resumes execution until next breakpoint
- **Register display**: `r`/`regs` shows full CPU state (A,X,Y,SP,PC,P,cycles)
- **Disassembly**: `d [addr] [n]` disassembles n instructions from addr
- **Memory dump**: `m addr [len]` hex+ASCII dump
- **Stack display**: `stack` shows stack contents from SP to $01FF
- **VIA inspection**: `via` shows all VIA 6522 registers, timers, IRQ status
- **PSG inspection**: `psg` shows AY-3-8910 registers, channels, envelope
- **Register modification**: `set reg val` modifies CPU registers at runtime
- **Quit**: `q`/`quit` stops emulator from debugger
- **Help**: `h`/`help` shows command reference
- **`include/emulator.h`**: extracted `emulator_t` struct from `src/main.c`
  into shared header for access by debugger and future modules
- **CLI option `--debug` / `-D`**: start in debugger mode (break at first instruction)
- **CLI option `--break ADDR`**: set initial debugger breakpoint (hex address)
- **F9 key**: enter interactive debugger during SDL2 emulation
- **Legacy breakpoint promotion**: existing `-b`/`--breakpoint` now enters
  interactive debugger instead of halting
- **8 debugger unit tests** in `tests/unit/test_debugger.c`:
  init state, add/remove breakpoints, breakpoint limit (16 max),
  add/remove watchpoints, breakpoint hit/miss, step mode, disassembly
- **`make test-debugger`** target added
- **Valgrind target** updated to include debugger tests

#### Changed
- `emulator_t` struct moved from `src/main.c` to `include/emulator.h`
- `emulator_t` now includes `debugger_t debugger` member
- Version updated from 1.0.0-rc to 1.1.0-alpha
- Makefile: added `src/debugger.c` to SOURCES, test-debugger target
- CMakeLists.txt: added DEBUGGER_SOURCES, debugger_tests target
- .gitignore: added `test_debugger`
- Test suite expanded from 155 to 163 tests (155 + 8 debugger)
- Total test count: 163 tests, 100% pass rate

